com.azure.data.appconfiguration.models

Class SettingSelector

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.azure.data.appconfiguration.models.SettingSelector

  • public class SettingSelector
extends java.lang.Object
    A set of options for selecting configuration settings from App Configuration service.
    • Providing labels will filter ConfigurationSettings that match any label name in conjunction with the keys that are passed in to the service request.
    • Providing acceptDateTime will return the representation of matching ConfigurationSetting at that given OffsetDateTime.
    • Providing fields will populate only those ConfigurationSetting fields in the response. By default, all of the fields are returned.
    See Also:
    ConfigurationAsyncClient

    • Method Detail

      • keys

        public java.lang.String[] keys()
        Gets the expressions to filter keys on for the request.

        Examples:

        1. If keys = "*", settings with any key are returned.
        2. If keys = "abc1234", settings with a key equal to "abc1234" are returned.
        3. If keys = "abc*", settings with a key starting with "abc" are returned.
        4. If keys = "*abc*", settings with a key containing "abc" are returned.
        Returns:
        The expressions to filter ConfigurationSetting keys on.

      • keys

        public SettingSelector keys(java.lang.String... keys)
        Sets the expressions to filter keys on for the request.

        Examples:

        • If keys = "*", settings with any key are returned.
        • If keys = "abc1234", settings with a key equal to "abc1234" are returned.
        • If keys = "abc*", settings with a key starting with "abc" are returned.
        • If keys = "*abc*", settings with a key containing "abc" are returned.
        • If keys = "abc,def", settings with a key equal to "abc" or "def" are returned.
        Parameters:
        keys - The expressions to filter ConfigurationSetting keys on.
        Returns:
        The updated SettingSelector object

      • labels

        public java.lang.String[] labels()
        Gets the labels used to filter settings based on their label in the service. If the value is null or an empty string, all ConfigurationSettings with ConfigurationSetting.NO_LABEL are returned.

        Examples:

        • If labels = "*", settings with any label are returned.
        • If labels = "\0", settings without any label are returned.
        • If labels = "", settings without any label are returned.
        • If labels = null, settings without any label are returned.
        • If labels = "abc1234", settings with a label equal to "abc1234" are returned.
        • If labels = "abc*", settings with a label starting with "abc" are returned.
        • If labels = "*abc*", settings with a label containing "abc" are returned.
        • If labels = "abc,def", settings with labels "abc" or "def" are returned.
        Returns:
        labels The labels used to filter GET requests from the service.

      • labels

        public SettingSelector labels(java.lang.String... labels)
        Sets the query to match labels in the service.

        Examples:

        • If labels = "*", settings with any label are returned.
        • If labels = "\0", settings without any label are returned. (This is the default label.)
        • If labels = "abc1234", settings with a label equal to "abc1234" are returned.
        • If labels = "abc*", settings with a label starting with "abc" are returned.
        • If labels = "*abc*", settings with a label containing "abc" are returned.
        • If labels = "abc,def", settings with labels "abc" or "def" are returned.
        Parameters:
        labels - The ConfigurationSetting labels to match. If the provided value is null or "", all ConfigurationSettings will be returned regardless of their label.
        Returns:
        SettingSelector The updated SettingSelector object.

      • acceptDateTime

        public java.lang.String acceptDateTime()
        Gets the date time for the request query. When the query is performed, if acceptDateTime is set, the configuration setting value at that point in time is returned. Otherwise, the current value is returned.
        Returns:
        Gets the currently set datetime in DateTimeFormatter.RFC_1123_DATE_TIME format.

      • acceptDatetime

        public SettingSelector acceptDatetime(java.time.OffsetDateTime datetime)
        If set, then configuration setting values will be retrieved as they existed at the provided datetime. Otherwise, the current values are returned.
        Parameters:
        datetime - The value of the configuration setting at that given OffsetDateTime.
        Returns:
        The updated SettingSelector object.
